version: 1
project: vokda
repo: iksnae/vokda
description: >
  Vokda is the central destination for everything TTS — a voice discovery and curation platform
  (Pinterest for voices) combined with an industry hub tracking new models, news, reviews, and
  guidance. It covers 550+ voices across 25 providers and 53 languages, with a SvelteKit 4
  frontend, AWS Amplify Gen2 backend (Cognito + AppSync + DynamoDB), and a SAM-deployed
  serverless synthesis API with 9 provider adapters and BYOK credential management.

models:
  planner: claude-sonnet-4-6
  builder: claude-sonnet-4-6
  escalation: claude-sonnet-4-6
  reviewer: claude-haiku-4-5

validate:
  - name: Unit Tests
    run: "npm test"

ci_check: true

context: |
  ## Architecture
  - **Frontend** (`apps/web`): SvelteKit 4 with static adapter. All routes under `apps/web/src/routes/`.
  - **Catalog**: `apps/web/static/data/voices.json` — source of truth (550 voices, 53 languages). Never edit directly; regenerate via `node scripts/publish-catalog.mjs`.
  - **Auth**: Cognito user pools via `aws-amplify`. Role hierarchy: visitor → guest → curator → admin. Groups defined in `amplify/auth/resource.ts`.
  - **Data layer**: Amplify Data (AppSync + 10 DynamoDB tables) — `amplify/data/resource.ts`. Models: favorites, collections, credentials, clips, VoiceRecord, ProviderRecord, VoiceReview, UserProfile, UserStorage, APIKey.
  - **Synthesis API** (`infra/`): SAM-deployed Lambda + API Gateway + SQS + S3. Entry: `infra/functions/synthesis-router/index.mjs`. 9 provider adapters in `lib/adapters/`. Auth via `auth-authorizer/` (JWT + `vk_live_...` API keys).
  - **Admin API** (`apps/api/src/server.mjs`): Node.js HTTP server for user role management.

  ## Key Files
  - `apps/web/src/lib/types.ts` — all shared TypeScript types
  - `apps/web/src/lib/catalog.ts` — catalog loader (fetches voices.json)
  - `apps/web/src/lib/voice-catalog.ts` — metadata patching, effective catalog builder
  - `apps/web/src/lib/stores/app-state.ts` — collections, favorites, curation state
  - `apps/web/src/lib/stores/clips.ts` — API-backed clip store
  - `apps/web/src/lib/synthesis/service.ts` — synthesis orchestration
  - `apps/web/src/lib/ssml/` — SSML tags, validation, serialization
  - `amplify/data/resource.ts` — AppSync schema (10 models)
  - `infra/template.yaml` — SAM template

  ## Environment Variables
  - `PUBLIC_AUTH_MODE`: `amplify` (production) or `mock` (local dev without Cognito)
  - `PUBLIC_SYNTHESIS_API_URL`: `https://api.vokda.iksnae.com`
  - Auth configured via `amplify_outputs.json` — never modify directly, generated by `ampx`

  ## Monorepo Workspace Layout
  - `apps/web` — SvelteKit frontend (`@vokda/web`)
  - `apps/api` — admin API server
  - `amplify/` — Amplify Gen2 backend definition
  - `infra/` — SAM template + Lambda functions
  - `packages/sdk` — SDK package (in progress)

  ## Code Patterns
  - SvelteKit pages use `export let data` for page props, `$:` reactive statements
  - Stores: `svelte/store` writable/derived; use `import { get } from 'svelte/store'` for snapshots
  - CSS: component-scoped `<style>` blocks — no global CSS framework
  - IDs: ULIDs for voices/variants/samples
  - Dates: ISO 8601 strings; Amplify models use `createdAtIso`/`updatedAtIso`
  - TypeScript strict mode throughout — no `any` without justification

  ## Current Phase
  Phase 1 (Active) — Catalog Quality & Polish. Critical gap: favorites/collections still in
  localStorage, not yet wired to Amplify Data DynamoDB backend.

  ## Do Not Touch
  - `amplify_outputs.json` — generated by `ampx`, never hand-edit
  - `.svelte-kit/`, `build/`, `.amplify/artifacts/`, `node_modules/`
  - `apps/web/static/data/voices.json` — regenerate via publish-catalog.mjs, don't hand-edit

guardrails:
  - Never commit .env files or secrets of any kind
  - Never modify amplify_outputs.json directly — it is generated by ampx
  - Never modify files under .svelte-kit/, build/, .amplify/artifacts/, or node_modules/
  - Keep voice catalog data in apps/web/static/data/voices.json as source of truth; regenerate via scripts/publish-catalog.mjs
  - TypeScript strict mode — no `any` unless absolutely necessary with justification comment
  - No floating promises — always await or explicitly handle
  - No swallowed errors — catch blocks must log or rethrow
  - Strict equality (===) throughout
  - CSS is component-scoped in <style> blocks — do not introduce global CSS frameworks
  - Auth mode is controlled by PUBLIC_AUTH_MODE env var — never hardcode auth provider

standards:
  language: TypeScript
  framework: SvelteKit 4
  runtime: Node.js 20+
  backend: AWS Amplify Gen2 (Cognito + AppSync + DynamoDB)
  api: SAM-deployed Lambda + API Gateway
  test_framework: vitest
  id_format: ULID
  date_format: ISO 8601 strings
  css: component-scoped Svelte style blocks
  strict_mode: true

curator:
  ignore_labels: ["question", "wontfix", "duplicate", "dependencies", "invalid"]
  ignore_authors: ["dependabot[bot]", "renovate[bot]", "github-actions[bot]", "amplify-bot[bot]"]
